# PlantGuard-AI configuration — copy to `.env` and fill in to enable LLM reasoning.
# Everything works WITHOUT these set: the agent falls back to the offline,
# citation-backed knowledge base so the demo always runs.

# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
# Reasoning LLM — Option A: Azure AI Foundry / Azure OpenAI (recommended for the
# Microsoft Agents League submission)
# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
# AZURE_OPENAI_ENDPOINT=https://<your-resource>.openai.azure.com
# AZURE_OPENAI_API_KEY=<your-azure-openai-key>
# AZURE_OPENAI_DEPLOYMENT=gpt-4o-mini
# AZURE_OPENAI_API_VERSION=2024-08-01-preview

# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
# Reasoning LLM — Option B: any OpenAI-compatible endpoint
# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
# OPENAI_API_KEY=<your-key>
# OPENAI_BASE_URL=https://api.openai.com/v1
# OPENAI_MODEL=gpt-4o-mini

# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
# Microsoft Foundry IQ — grounded knowledge retrieval (the Microsoft IQ layer)
# Foundry IQ knowledge bases are backed by Azure AI Search agentic retrieval.
# The endpoint is your Search service URL; the key is a Search admin/query key.
# When unset, foundry.py grounds answers with the bundled curated agronomy KB.
#
# Setup: in the Foundry portal (ai.azure.com) -> Build -> Knowledge, connect an
# Azure AI Search service and create a knowledge base from a knowledge source
# (e.g. agronomy docs in Azure Blob Storage). Free path: Azure AI Search free
# tier + "minimal" reasoning effort (no LLM) stays within the free allocation.
# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
# FOUNDRY_IQ_ENDPOINT=https://<your-search-service>.search.windows.net
# FOUNDRY_IQ_API_KEY=<your-azure-ai-search-admin-or-query-key>
# FOUNDRY_IQ_KNOWLEDGE_BASE=plantguard-agri-kb
# Optional — name + kind of a specific knowledge source (enables citations):
# FOUNDRY_IQ_KNOWLEDGE_SOURCE=plantguard-agri-source
# FOUNDRY_IQ_KNOWLEDGE_SOURCE_KIND=azureBlob          # searchIndex|azureBlob|web|sharepoint
# Optional — retrieval reasoning effort: minimal (no LLM, free) | low | medium
# FOUNDRY_IQ_REASONING_EFFORT=minimal
# FOUNDRY_IQ_API_VERSION=2026-05-01-preview

# Optional: request timeout in seconds (default 30)
# PLANTGUARD_TIMEOUT=30
